== Cucumber Tomato Salad ==

Wash and dry produce. Trim and dice half the @cucumber{1} into ½-inch pieces. Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

> Use the whole cucumber for 4 servings.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce} and @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Stir in cucumber and tomato; season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

== Avocado Sauce ==

In a second medium bowl, combine @guacamole{4%tablespoon} and remaining @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Perfectly Poached Eggs ==

Pour ½ cup water into each of two #microwave-safe mugs{}. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Carefully crack one @egg{2} into each mug and tightly cover mug with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until egg whites are set and yolks are cooked to preference, ~{50-60%seconds} more (times may vary based on microwave power; if needed, continue to microwave in ~{10%seconds} intervals until eggs reach desired doneness). Using a #slotted spoon{}, carefully transfer eggs to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}; discard water. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, repeat to cook remaining eggs.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.

== Assembly ==

Toast @sourdough bread{2%slice} until golden in a #toaster{}. Divide between #plates{}; spread with creamy avocado sauce. Top with cucumber tomato salad, @feta cheese{½%cup}, and eggs; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Serve.